title: lana_isavia
body:
A main character from [[choujikuu_kidan_southern_cross|The Super Dimension Cavalry Southern Cross]] [[mecha]] anime series from the 80s.

[b]Lana Isavia[/b] is a member of the [[GMP]] (Glorie Military Police), a [[MP]] unit used to keep the other military units in check.

Despite what her youthful appearance could suggest, she is actually a very serious and mature character devoted entirely to her duties.

Her name in the [[ROBOTECH]] western adaptation was changed to [b]Nova Satori[/b].

title: lyra_(re:zero)
body:
Lyra is an exclusive character from the video game [[re:zero kara hajimeru isekai seikatsu: lost in memories|Re:Zero Lost in Memories]]. She is a phantom that was created by [[shion (re:zero)|Shion]] and is one of the antagonists of the game.

Lyra has [[long hair|long]] [[purple hair]] with [[blunt bangs]] and two [[black flower|black]] [[hair flower|Mariposa lilies]] on her hair. Her clothes are almost similar to Shion's, however, unlike Shion, her attire was more revealing as she consists of a short [[black dress|black]] [[sleeveless dress|sleeveless]] [[frilled dress]] and [[black gloves]]. She adorns herself with a crimson [[red rose]] on her left arm, a [[dagger]] wrapped around her hips, and a small gold locket around her neck with a purple bow as a choker.

title: color_banding
body:
Color banding is a form of image artefacting found in low bit depth images, where the lack of bits cause colors to be rounded rather than blending smothly together. The result is a series of "bands" of colors, where one shade will suddenly jump to the next, rather than fading smoothly together.

h4. See also

* [[dithering]]
* [[gif artifacts]]

title: gif_artifacts
body:
The [[Animated GIF]] image format is made to display a maximum of 256 colors in one image.  When an image containing more than 256 colors is saved as a GIF, the color limitation of the GIF format creates artifacts (defects) such as [[dithering]] (e.g. post #720057) or [[color banding]] (e.g. the background of post #76332).

Note that despite artifacting in high-color images, GIFs have legitimate uses, such as for [[pixel art]], low-color [[Oekaki]] images, and animated images.

h4. See also

* [[tag group:image composition]]

title: steel_square
body:
A [i]steel square[/i], also commonly referred to as a [i]framing square[/i] or [i]carpenter's square[/i], is a tool used in carpentry.  It is a long-armed square (a tool used for marking and referencing a 90° angle) consisting of a wider arm and shorter, narrower arm, that meet at a right angle.  Traditionally made of steel, they're also commonly now made of other materials such as aluminum.

The longer wider arm is two inches (51 mm) wide, and is called the blade; the shorter narrower arm, is one and a half inches (38 mm) wide, and is called the tongue. The square has many uses, including laying out common rafters, hip rafters and stairs.  It has a diagonal scale, board foot scale and an octagonal scale. On the newer squares there are degree conversions for different pitches and fractional equivalents.

title: periscope
body:
A periscope is an instrument for observation over, around or through an object or obstacle that prevents direct line-of-sight.  In its simplest form, it consists of an outer case with mirrors at each end set parallel to each other at a 45° angle. 

Periscopes are most commonly remembered for their use in [[submarine]]s, but have been used by the military in other areas such as trench warfare, gun turrets, and armored vehicles.  Periscopes in the use of submarines have gradually been replaced by the [i]photonics mast[/i], a similar device that replaces the direct mechanical line-of-sight with digital equipment and cameras.

Horses and Thoroughbreds are better explained in [[Brown Thoroughbred (Kemono Friends)|]]'s page.

A white horse denotes a horse with a white coat (or a coat splotched with white) with pink skin, caused by a dominant white gene, usually created from a random fortuitous mutation. For this reason, white in Thoroughbreds is very rare and few thrive in the racetrack simply due to demographics (for example, only [[sodashi_(racehorse)|one white horse]] has ever won a 1st grade race and only as recently as 2020, this one eventually won two more races of that grade). They are not to be confused with gray horses, horses who, born as chestnut or bay, become lighter in color with age, eventually ending up with a white coat and dark skin.

White Thoroughbred is (naturally) a [[horse girl]] with long white hair resembling a mane in braids, wearing a white sports ensemble.

title: off-shoulder_leotard
body:

For the leotard to qualify for this tag, the sleeves [i]must be attached[/i] to the leotard. If they are not, then it is a [[strapless leotard]] with [[detached sleeves]].

Off-shoulder leotards and [[strapless leotard]]s are mutually exclusive to each other.

title: jure_of_healing
body:
Jure of Healing is the goddess of restorative magic in [[Elona]], and the goddess whose religion seems most traditionally similar to Christianity, including a "Festival of Jure" that happens during December.  (Which also functions as a membership drive/evangelization for her religion.)  Her divine weapon is also The Holy Lance, a spear that heals its user, a reference to the Christian belief that the spear that pierced the side of Christ became a holy relic capable of miracles.

She appears as a woman with white feathery [[wings]], a yellow dress and broad-topped hat, and [[green hair]] with a copper-colored stripe.  

Jure is, unusual for her seeming Christian inspiration, a [[tsundere]], and seems quite insecure around her own followers.  In stereotypical tsundere fashion, she stutters while saying that she really doesn't want you to be her follower, or denying that she's happy when you give her sacrifices or that she's been lonely if you have closed the game for a while.

Her preferred sacrifices are ores, which are the subject of a few jokes, as ores can be both valuable materials like rubynus crystals, or useless junk stones.  Nearly every player sacrifices junk stones to her, however, as they are rewarded just the same, and are far less valuable and more easily found in literally any random field by the side of the road.  Hence, it's common to see Jure being inundated with junk stone sacrifices.

Jure's servants are the [[Defender (elona)|]]s.

title: black_angel_(elona)
body:
A divine servant character of the sadistic [[Lulwy of Wind]], [[Black Angel (elona)|]]s are given as rewards to Lulwy's faithful in the game [[Elona]].  

Their salient characteristics are their [[purple hair]] in [[twintails]],  with black ribbons, their characteristic [[black wings]], blue frilly dress, and black boots.  

The twintails, alone, give many artists a "tsundere" impression of Black Angel, although given her master's sadism, some show her quite masochistic, as well.  

Like most Elona characters, they are randomly named upon spawning, and Black Angel is just a class name.  In-game, they appear as something like "Anita the black angel". 

As the servant of the most archery-centric goddess, black angels are most commonly wielding a [[bow (weapon)|]], but can use any melee weapon.  Their specialty is a self-targeting speed boost, which lets them rain arrows upon their opponents in rapid succession.

title: lind
body:
Lind is an [[Aa Megami-sama]] character, and a Valkyrie: goddess that belongs to Heaven's Fighting Wings combat unit. In the manga she's the fifth goddess to show up in [[Morisato Keiichi|Keiichi's]] house, during an emergency, although in the anime, she makes a brief appearance before that, making her the fourth goddess to appear on screen. 

Serious, stoic and all business like, are the best ways to describe Lind, even though she does have a sensitive side to her as well. Lind had to struggle for quite some to overcome a rather unusual condition that left her with an angel that possessed one wing (and even referred to as the [i]"One winged angel"[/i]) but in the end it was proven that she had a pair of twin angels. Being unable to support both of them at the same time, Lind pushed herself harder than any other Valkyrie, earning herself a rather fearsome reputation among Heavens. Eventually, Lind overcomes her difficulties, and thanks to the involvement of Keiichi in the entire process, she likens to refer to him as her lifelong friend.

title: defender_(elona)
body:
The [[Defender (elona)|]] is the divine servant of the goddess [[Jure of Healing]] in the game [[Elona]], and become party members of the faithful of Jure.  Defenders are basically the game's equivalent to a paladin, and have high defensive traits and a unique ability to raise fallen allies from death once per day.  

Salient characteristics of the are short [[brown hair]], brown [[armor]], and a dark [[cape]].

Defenders are one of the few servants that are always male. 

Like many characters in Elona, Defender is just a "class name", and names for defenders are randomly generated upon spawning, meaning that they appear as something like "Nodestan the defender" in-game.

title: black_cat_(elona)
body:
Servant of [[Ehekatl of Luck]], luck goddess of [[Elona]], black cats can become party members as rewards for those who are faithful to the quirky goddess. 

Appearance-wise, the black cat is... well, a black [[cat]]. 

Amusingly, due to the way that the race of all servants is "servant" race, black cats have a humanoid form, size, and weight in game stats terms, even though they appear as cats.  This means they can wear plate armor and wield sword and shield or use guns.  

Their special ability is "licking" the items dropped by some of the creatures they kill, adding one extra magical effect to the randomly-generated equipment.

Black cats can either be male or female... although there's no particular difference unless they are evolved in Elona+, where male black cats become black [[lion]]s, and female black cats become catgirls.  

Like many characters in Elona, black cat is just a "class name" for the character, and they have a randomly generated personal name upon spawning.  Hence, they would appear as something such as "Sezluk the black cat".

title: pythia
body:
[b]Pythia[/b] (pronounced /ˈpɪθiə/ or /ˈpaɪθiə/, Greek: Πυθία [pyːˈtʰi.a]), commonly known as [b]the Oracle of Delphi[/b], was the priestess at the Greek Temple of Apollo at Delphi, located on the slopes of Mount Parnassus. Pythia was widely credited for her prophecies inspired by God [[Apollo (mythology)|]]. 

The Delphic [[Oracle (ancient greece)|]] was established in the 8th century BCE. The last recorded response was given during AD 393, when the emperor Theodosius I ordered pagan temples to cease operation.

During this period the Delphic Oracle was the most prestigious and authoritative oracle among the Greeks.

title: kumiromi_of_harvest
body:
Kumiromi of Harvest is the god of agriculture in [[Elona]].

Appearance-wise, his salient features are a green tunic, a green jester's hat, short [[brown hair]], white feathery [[wings]], and rather feminine appearance.  (There was initially some confusion as to his actual gender.)  He often wields his characteristic [[scythe]].

Personality-wise, he is a quiet sort that generally enjoys nature and watching over the growth of living things.  He only speaks complete sentences when talking about enjoying nature.  He admonishes his followers for spreading death, unlike most other gods.  His comments imply he is a former lover of [[Ehekatl of Luck]]'s, but her personality transformed, and they grew distant.  Kumiromi makes comments mourning this change on occasion.  Unlike most gods, rewards for following him are crafting-based skills and items.

Kumiromi does have what appears to be a dark side, however, and bears a grudge against those who betray him for another god or attack him, turning apparently [[yandere]] in the process, although he becomes no less terse about it.

His favored sacrifices are [[seed]]s and any form of [[vegetable]], even cooked, rotten, or rotten cooked ones.  Players that serve him often cook rotten vegetables and sacrifice them to him to train their cooking and not waste rotten food.  (Seeds are too rare and valuable to sacrifice.)

His servants are the [[cute_fairy_(elona)|cute fairies]].

title: opatos_of_earth
body:
Opatos of Earth is the god of strength in [[Elona]].  

He appears as a muscle-bound masculine figure that has giant stone [[wings]], is walking apparently out of a rock formation, or else has legs that disappear into stone, and inhumanly long arms made of stone. He wears a [[blindfold]]. He has long [[blue hair]], but some artists show it as brown, as well.

He tends to be a jovial sort, laughing even when angry.  Reckless and emotional, he is portrayed as the sort who acts upon feeling, and rarely thinks things through.  

He likes ore as his sacrifices, and he gives out a hammer as his divine weapon.

His servants are the [[golden_knight_(elona)|Golden Knights]].

title: mani_of_machine
body:
God of machines in [[Elona]].  He has a laid-back and level-headed personality.  He claims that the replacement of all organic life with machinery is an inevitability in some of his dialogue, but otherwise does not show any hostility towards anyone besides some rivalry towards the other gods.  

Appearance-wise, his salient features are white hair, and red eyes on a handsome humanoid head, with the rest of his body being clearly mechanical, with a black armored torso covered by black clothing and a [[cape]].  His metallic hands and torso have [[doll joints]].

His preferred sacrifice is a [[gun]], and his personal weapon he gives to players who are exceptionally devoted is a type of [[shotgun]] called the Winchester Premium.

His servants are the [[Android (elona)|]]s.

title: exile_(elona)
body:
The [[exile_(elona)|Exile]] is the divine servant of [[Itzpalt of Element]], the god of magic in the game [[Elona]].  As such, they are the only wizard-type servants in the game.  Servants can become party members as a divine reward when the player has a high enough devotion in a given deity's religion.  

In-game, the exiles appear as red-robed figures whose face is obscured by a hood, but which have [[third eye|three]] [[red eyes]], and a staff held by a strangely gray arm.  Different artists portray them differently, sometimes as long-haired and otherwise handsome characters with gray cancerous-looking lesions or partly petrified characters.  

In Elona+, they have one of the most sexually dimorphic evolutions of all the pets.  Male exiles turn into black [[dragon]]s, while female exiles turn into beautiful, but still three-eyed [[witch]]es in moderately revealing outfits, as opposed to their fully-hidden figures before. 

Like most Elona characters, Exile is just a "class name", and their actual names will be randomly generated upon spawning.  Hence, in-game, they would appear as something like "Omikka the exile".

title: yu-gi-oh!_duel_monsters
body:
The original [[Yu-Gi-Oh!]] series. Known in Japan as Yu-Gi-Oh! Duel Monsters and is an anime based on the Yu-Gi-Oh! manga ([[Yu-Gi-Oh! (Toei)|minus the early parts]]). Produced by Studio Gallop and Nihon Ad Systems. Written by [[Takahashi Kazuki]].

The series began its 224-episode run in Japan on April 18, 2000 and ended on September 29, 2004. In the United States, it began airing on September 29, 2001 and ended on June 10, 2006.

After the positive reception following the release of the official card game by [[Konami]] in 1999, the series marked the point where it transitioned from a dark fantasy to almost exclusively revolving around the "Duel Monsters" card game. The series' "Duelist Kingdom" arc is also (in)famously known within the community for retaining the RPG-like elements from the early part of the manga, resulting in several unconventional uses of the cards (such as the notorious "attack the moon" scene and fusing a zombie monster to an opponent's monster and causing it to rot).

h4. Characters
See [[List of Yu-Gi-Oh! characters]]

title: shinobi_(ps2)
body:
[b][i]Shinobi (PS2)[/i][/b] is a 3D action-adventure [[video game]] developed by Overworks and published by [[SEGA]] as part of the [[shinobi_(game)|Shinobi series]]. 

It was released for the [[PlayStation 2]] console on November 10, 2002 in North America; December 5 in Japan; and May 15, 2003 in Europe. 

The game stars a [[ninja]] master called [[Hotsuma]], leader of the Oboro clan, who wields Akujiki, a sword that feeds on souls. He can also use ninja magic, shurikens, and special moves. 

Shinobi was originally planned for the [[Sega Dreamcast]], but due to the discontinuation of the console, the game was moved to the PS2. The title was designed to place emphasis on the action elements of action-adventure gameplay and appeal to the action market. Other gameplay elements resulted from a desire to mix old and new elements. Upon release, Shinobi was generally well received by critics. A comic book adaptation, soundtrack album, and sequel entitled [[kunoichi_(game)|Kunoichi]] were also released.

title: green_dam
body:
Green Dam Girl (绿坝娘, [i]lǜ bà niáng[/i]) is a [[personification]] of the [[China|Chinese]] government's DRM and filtering software "绿坝·花季护航 ([i]Luba Huaji Huhang[/i], Green Dam Youth Escort)" as well as an alternate personification of "[[Great Firewall|The Great Firewall]]" (China's elaborate internet censorship algorithm).

At first, her figure resembled [[Kawashiro Nitori]]. But later, her various designs appeared. In most versions, she either wears a hat with the symbol of "'河蟹 ([i]hexie[/i], River crab)'":[http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Harmonious_society#River_crab] or having a [[green hair|green]] [[twintails]] and [[red eyes]].

The word "Green Dam" were later used by both the Chinese netizens and outsiders as a shorthand term for the Chinese internet censorship (and various censorship deployed by the CCP in general). As such, Green Dam Girl has gained similar recurring [[meme]] status as [[Jiang Zemin]] within the Chinese internet community.

She has regionally various names. If you're searching for her pictures in [[Pixiv]], try all these tag names:

* Simplified Chinese: 绿坝娘 (Lu ba niang) or 格林达姆 (Green Dam) or 绿⑧ (Lu ba)
* Traditional Chinese: 綠壩娘 (Lu ba niang)
* Japanese: 緑bar娘 or 緑bar子 (Lu ba niang) or グリーンダム (Green Dam) or グリーンダムたん (Green dam-tan)
* English: Green Dam Girl

h4.See also

* [[Blue Dam]]

title: nagumo_chuuichi
body:
(25 March 1887 – 6 July 1944) 

[[Imperial Japanese Navy]] admiral known as the commander of the Pearl Harbor/Indian Ocean task force (Kido Butai) before being infamous for his command at the [[battle of Midway]] where all four carriers in his task force were ambushed and sunk.

In the aforementioned battle, he elected to wait for the return of the first Midway strike before launching his planes against the US forces against [[Yamaguchi Tamon]]'s suggestions and prodding to launch as soon as the US carriers were sighted. The waves of attacks by US torpedo bombers prevented Nagumo from giving out the order to launch before the dive bombers arrived and dealt the fatal blows to three of his four carriers, including [[Akagi (aircraft carrier)|his own flagship]].

He never fully recovered mentally from the disastrous battle and, after repeated reassignments, ultimately committed suicide in the battle of Saipan in July 1944.

title: albino
body:
Complete or partial absence of skin and hair pigment due to an absence or defect of an enzyme needed for the production of melanin. Due to this, people and animals appear very light-skinned and typically have red eyes because while there is no pigment in the irises, the blood vessels can still be seen. This does not disqualify blue eyes, however, as most people with ocular albinism have blue eyes that bear a slight red tint due to the blood vessel still present. 

Characters with albinism [b]must[/b] have the following to qualify:

* Either [[white_hair|white]] or [[grey_hair|grey]] hair.
* [[red_eyes|Red]], [[blue_eyes|blue]], [[pink_eyes|pink]] or [[purple_eyes|purple]] eyes.
* [[pale skin|Pale]] or [[white skin|white]] skin.

title: souzu
body:
A type of [[shishi odoshi|Shishi-odoshi]]. The true name of "the thing that goes doink". 

Souzu are bamboo tubes with one end closed that are balanced on a fulcrum, and placed at the base of a fountain, such that they gradually fill with water. When the tube is full, the weight of the water causes it to tip over and pour the water out, which quickly shifts the weight back to the closed end, causing it to hit the ground and make a sharp "donk". Souzu are traditionally used to scare deer away from gardens by startling them with the sound, and are a sign of affluence and wealth.

http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shishi-odoshi

Kichiboushi is a bake-danuki who gave Ioroi company. He was sealed alongside many of his kin by Kamuna Harunosuke; however, as Harunosuke did not properly seal all of the bake-danuki away, some of them were able to escape their confinement, Kichiboushi being one of them. During the events of cleansing the Sacred Sakura, Ioroi has Kichiboushi bring the Traveler and Paimon bring them to the corrupted Sakura roots underneath Chinju Forest.

Some time afterwards, Paimon and Traveler decided to visit Ioroi on a whim. Ioroi, remarking on the other lands he saw prior to his petrification and that he had no knowledge of them, decided to have Kichiboushi accompany the two outside Inazuma as he was excited to play with them again and wanted to train more. When the Traveler remarked that they wanted to talk with Kichiboushi during their travels, Ioroi gave them a bake-danuki feast so they could understand what Kichibouchi was saying. The training mostly consisted of taking Kichiboushi around various places across Mondstadt and Liyue.

At the end of the trip, Kichiboushi was brought back to Chinju Forest and promised to uphold and remember what the Traveler and Paimon had taught him.

title: mega_man_2
body:
[b]Rocman 2[/b], known outside of [[Japan]] as [b]Mega Man 2[/b], is a 2D action [[video game]] developed and published by [[Capcom]] for the [[Nintendo]] [[Famicom]]/Nintendo  Entertainment System. 

It was released in Japan in 1988 and in North America and PAL regions the following years. Mega Man 2 continues the heroic [[android]] [[mega_man_(character)|Mega Man]]'s battle against the evil [[dr._wily_(mega_man)|Dr. Wily]] and his rogue [[robot]]s. It introduced graphical and gameplay changes, many of which became series staples.

Although sales for the [[mega_man_1|original Mega Man]] were unimpressive, Capcom allowed the team to create a sequel. They worked concurrently on other Capcom projects, using their free time to develop the game, using unused content from the first game. Tateishi Takashi composed the soundtrack, with Sakaguchi Yoshihiro serving as a sound programmer.

[b]Mega Man 2 is the bestselling Mega Man game of all time[/b], with more than 1.5 million copies sold. Critics praised its audio, visuals and gameplay as an improvement over the first game. Many publications rank Mega Man 2 as the best game in the series and one of the greatest video games of all time. 

It has been featured in game compilations, including Mega Man Legacy Collection for Windows, [[PlayStation 4]], [[Xbox One]], [[Nintendo 3DS]], and [[Nintendo Switch]], become a part of console emulation services, and appeared on mobile phones.

title: matias_torres
body:
The main antagonist from [[Ace Combat 7]]'s SP missions. Formerly a gunnery officer for the Erusean Navy up to the events of the [[ace_combat_04|Continental War]], he would earn the popular title as [i]The Hero of Comberth Harbor[/i] after he saved the crew of the "ship he was assigned to":[https://acecombat.fandom.com/wiki/Tanager] during an air raid by [[isaf|ISAF]] air forces. Years later he would become the captain of an advanced submersible aviation cruiser named [[Alicorn (Ace Combat)|]], but the submarine accidentally ran aground and was missing for 698 days, eventually being found with most of its crew miraculously alive. During the events of the [[ace_combat_7|Lighthouse War]], the Erusean Navy didn't consider the submarine as part of their battle doctrine. After [[Trigger (Ace Combat)|]]'s squadron and another squadron destroyed much of Erusea's main fleet, it was hastily commissioned to plug the sudden defecit in naval power.

However, Captain Matias Torres went rogue, determined to end the war in one fell swoop by nuking the Osean capital of Oured. Believing that he could save 10 million lives in Usea by claiming 1 million in Osea, Torres sailed the [i]Alicorn[/i] into firing position only to be intercepted by Trigger and an Osean surface action group. While the latter would be sunk by his vessel, Trigger would in turn score a killing blow against the vessel, the resulting catastrophic detonation killing Torres and his crew.

He was described by an [[david_north|weapons analyst]]: "A devil incarnate." His bombastic delivery and insane ramblings ("Crisp white sheets!", "Salvation!", etc.) would result in him gaining a particularly memetic status among Ace Combat fans.
